com.ibm.mobile.services.location.device.geo

Class IBMGeoAcquisitionPolicy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.mobile.services.location.device.geo.IBMGeoAcquisitionPolicy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class IBMGeoAcquisitionPolicy
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    Controls how Geo positions will be acquired. The IBMGeoAcquisitionPolicy class is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases.

    • Method Detail

      • getPowerSavingProfile

        public static IBMGeoAcquisitionPolicy getPowerSavingProfile()
        Used to save power. Accurate location information is not guaranteed.
        Returns:
        a policy with the following preset values:
        • enableHighAccuracy = false
        • minChangeTime = 300000 (5 minutes)
        • minChangeDistance = 1000 (1 kilometer)
        • maximumAge = 300000 (5 minutes)

      • getRoughTrackingProfile

        public static IBMGeoAcquisitionPolicy getRoughTrackingProfile()
        Used to track location, but at a rough granularity.
        Returns:
        a policy with the following preset values:
        • enableHighAccuracy = true
        • desiredAccuracy = 200 (200 meters)
        • minChangeTime = 30000 (30 seconds)
        • minChangeDistance = 50 (50 meters)
        • maximumAge = 60000 (60 seconds)

      • getLiveTrackingProfile

        public static IBMGeoAcquisitionPolicy getLiveTrackingProfile()
        Used to track location, and get the best position information available.
        Returns:
        a policy with the following preset values:
        • enableHighAccuracy = true
        • maximumAge = 100 (100 milliseconds)

      • getMaximumAge

        public double getMaximumAge()
        Returns:
        the maximum age. A cached position can be returned from acquisition if the age of that position is less than the returned value. The default and minimum value is 100 milliseconds.

      • setMaximumAge

        public void setMaximumAge(long maximumAge)
        Set the maximum age of positions returned, in milliseconds. A cached position can be returned from acquisition if the age of that position is less than the specified value. The default and minimum value is 100 milliseconds.

      • getTimeout

        public long getTimeout()
        Returns:
        the duration, in milliseconds, this policy allows to wait for acquisitions before a IBMGeoError is sent with code IBMGeoError.GeoErrorCodes.TIMEOUT. -1 is used to indicate an infinite timeout

      • setTimeout

        public void setTimeout(long timeout)
        Set the timeout interval for position acquisition, specified in milliseconds. The default value is -1 which indicates an infinite timeout. If no position is acquired since the last position was acquired, or since IBMLocation#startAcquisition(com.ibm.mobile.services.location.IBMLocationConfiguration) was called, then the failure function will be called.

      • isEnableHighAccuracy

        public boolean isEnableHighAccuracy()
        Returns:
        true if it is possible to obtain high-accuracy measurements, for example by using GPS.

      • setEnableHighAccuracy

        public void setEnableHighAccuracy(boolean enableHighAccuracy)
        Control whether it is possible to obtain high-accuracy measurements, for example by using GPS. When true, the value of desiredAccuracy will be taken into account.

      • getDesiredAccuracy

        public int getDesiredAccuracy()
        Returns:
        the desired accuracy in meters. This is only taken into account when isEnableHighAccuracy() returns true.

      • setDesiredAccuracy

        public void setDesiredAccuracy(int desiredAccuracy)
        Set the desired accuracy in meters. This is only taken into account when isEnableHighAccuracy() returns true.

      • getMinChangeDistance

        public int getMinChangeDistance()
        Returns:
        the minimum distance in meters that the position must change by since the last update in order to receive a new updated position. The default value is 0.

      • setMinChangeDistance

        public void setMinChangeDistance(int minChangeDistance)
        Set the minimum distance in meters that the position must change by since the last update in order to receive a new updated position. Higher values can improve battery life, although the effect is generally less than that of setMinChangeTime(int). The default value is 0.
        Parameters:
        minChangeDistance - the minimum distance in meters that the position must change by since the last update in order to receive a new updated position.

      • getMinChangeTime

        public int getMinChangeTime()
        Returns:
        the minimum time in milliseconds between updates. The default value is 0.

      • setMinChangeTime

        public void setMinChangeTime(int minChangeTime)
        The minimum time in milliseconds between updates. Higher values can improve battery life.
